ugt-10 is an ortholog of human UGT3A2 (UDP glycosyltransferase family 3 member A2) and UGT3A1 (UDP glycosyltransferase family 3 member A1); ugt-10 is predicted to have transferase activity, transferring hexosyl groups, based on protein domain information.
T19H5.6 is predicted to have chitin binding activity, based on protein domain information.
T25B9.1 encodes an protein highly similar to 2-amino-3-keto-butyrate coenzyme A ligases (also called AKB ligases or glycine acetyltransferases; EC 2.3.1.29; R.W.
T25B9.9 is an ortholog of human Pgd (phosphogluconate dehydrogenase); T25B9.9 is predicted to have phosphogluconate dehydrogenase (decarboxylating) activity, based on protein domain information.
T26F2.1 is predicted to have chitinase activity, based on protein domain information.

T27F7.4 is an ortholog of human PIGB (phosphatidylinositol glycan anchor biosynthesis class B); T27F7.4 is predicted to have transferase activity, transferring glycosyl groups, based on protein domain information.
cah-6 encodes a predicted carbonic anhydrase.
tre-3 encodes one of four putative trehalases in C. elegans; tre-3 is expressed throughout development.

glct-6 is an ortholog of human B3GAT1 (beta-1,3-glucuronyltransferase 1), B3GAT3 (beta-1,3-glucuronyltransferase 3) and B3GAT2 (beta-1,3-glucuronyltransferase 2); glct-6 is predicted to have galactosylgalactosylxylosylprotein 3-beta-glucuronosyltransferase activity, based on protein domain information.
W10D5.2 is orthologous to the human gene NADH-UBIQUINONE OXIDOREDUCTASE Fe-S PROTEIN 7 (NDUFS7; OMIM:601825), which when mutated leads to Leigh syndrome (OMIM:256000).

Y105C5B.15 is an ortholog of human ACP7 (acid phosphatase 7, tartrate resistant (putative)); Y105C5B.15 is predicted to have acid phosphatase activity and metal ion binding activity, based on protein domain information.

Category 3: Signaling: heteromeric G protein: guanylyl cyclase
Description: gcy-25 encodes a predicted guanylate cyclase.
gln-3 is an ortholog of human GLUL (glutamate-ammonia ligase); gln-3 is predicted to have glutamate-ammonia ligase activity, based on protein domain information.

Y105C5B.3 is an ortholog of human ACP7 (acid phosphatase 7, tartrate resistant (putative)); Y105C5B.3 is predicted to have acid phosphatase activity and metal ion binding activity, based on protein domain information.
hpo-13 is an ortholog of human GBA2 (glucosylceramidase beta 2); hpo-13 is predicted to have glucosylceramidase activity, based on protein domain information.
yars-1 is an ortholog of human YARS (tyrosyl-tRNA synthetase); yars-1 is predicted to have ATP binding activity and aminoacyl-tRNA ligase activity, based on protein domain information.

Y105E8A.20 is an ortholog of human MARS2 (methionyl-tRNA synthetase 2, mitochondrial); Y105E8A.20 is predicted to have ATP binding activity and methionine-tRNA ligase activity, based on protein domain information.

rpom-1 is an ortholog of human POLRMT (RNA polymerase mitochondrial); rpom-1 is predicted to have DNA binding activity and DNA-directed 5'-3' RNA polymerase activity, based on protein domain information.
hprt-1 encodes an ortholog of human HYPOXANTHINE PHOSPHORIBOSYLTRANSFERASE 1 (HPRT1), which when mutated leads to Lesch-Nyhan syndrome (OMIM:308000).
Y105E8B.9 is orthologous to the human gene GLUTATHIONE TRANSFERASE ZETA 1 (MALEYLACETOACETATE ISOMERASE) (GUSB; OMIM:603758), which when mutated leads to disease.

set-33 encodes a putative histone H3 lysine-9 methyltransferase that is  predicted to function in transcriptional repression; SET-33 is paralogous  to SET-6, SET-15, SET-21, and SET-32; in mass RNAi assays, SET-33 is  required for embryonic and larval viability, normally large brood sizes,  and normally rapid growth.

Y10G11A.1 is an ortholog of human NT5C3A (5'-nucleotidase, cytosolic IIIA) and NT5C3B (5'-nucleotidase, cytosolic IIIB); Y10G11A.1 is predicted to have 5'-nucleotidase activity and magnesium ion binding activity, based on protein domain information.

hpo-20 is an ortholog of human PIGW (phosphatidylinositol glycan anchor biosynthesis class W); hpo-20 is predicted to have transferase activity, transferring acyl groups, based on protein domain information.

sqv-2 encodes a glycosaminoglycan galactosyltransferase II, biochemically active in vitro, that is required for cytokinesis of one-cell embryos and for vulval morphogenesis; the common requirement for SQV-2 in both cytokinesis and morphogenesis may be to promote filling an extracellular space with hygroscopic proteoglycans (either in the eggshell, or underneath the L4 cuticle), which in turn may cause the space to fill with fluid.

aap-1 encodes the C. elegans ortholog of the phosphoinositide 3-kinase (PI3K) p50/p55 adaptor/regulatory subunit; AAP-1 negatively regulates lifespan and dauer development, and likely functions as the sole adaptor subunit for the AGE-1/p110 PI3K catalytic subunit to which it binds in vitro; although AAP-1 potentiates insulin-like signaling, it is not absolutely required for insulin-like signaling under most conditions.

tyms-1 encodes the C. elegans thymidylate synthase ortholog; by homology, TYMS-1 is predicted to function in dTMP biosynthesis and thus in DNA synthesis; when expressed as a recombinant protein TYMS-1 exhibits thymidylate synthase activity in vitro, and this activity is negatively regulated by tyrosine nitration; analysis of crude C. elegans extracts indicates that thymidylate synthase activity is present in L1, L3, and dauer larval stages, as well as in adult animals.

pfkb-1.1 encodes a 6-phosphofructo-2-kinase/fructose-2,6-bisphosphatase (EC: 3.1.3.46) paralogous to PFKB-1.2; by homology, PFKB-1.1 is predicted to be a bifunctional enzyme that catalyzes the phosphorylation of fructose 6-phosphate and dephosphorylation of fructose 2,6-bisphosphate.

tpst-1 encodes a tyrosylprotein sulfotransferase; tpst-1 activity is required for proper cuticle formation and secretion of ROL-6, a cuticle collagen; when expressed in 293-T cells, TPST-1 exhibits tyrosylprotein sulfotransferase activity; a tpst-1::gfp promoter fusion is expressed beginning during embryogenesis and continuing through larval and adult stages; tpst-1 expression is seen mainly in the hypodermis, particularly the seam cells, and in head neurons.
bca-2 is involved in cellular metabolic process; bca-2 exhibits carbonate dehydratase activity and is predicted to have zinc ion binding activity, based on protein domain information.
gly-4 encodes a UDP-GalNAc:polypeptide N-acetylgalactosaminyltransferase; GLY-4 exhibits UDP-GalNAc:polypeptide N-acetylgalactosaminyltransferase activity in vitro.

ippk-1 is an ortholog of human IPPK (inositol-pentakisphosphate 2-kinase); ippk-1 is predicted to have ATP binding activity and inositol pentakisphosphate 2-kinase activity, based on protein domain information.
Y17G7B.3 is orthologous to the human gene HYDROXYACYLGLUTATHIONE HYDROLASE (HAGH; OMIM:138760), which when mutated leads to disease.
dhps-1 encodes a deoxyhypusine synthase; by homology, DHPS-1 is predicted to function in peptidyl-lysine modification to hypusine.

Y18D10A.3 is an ortholog of human YJEFN3 (YjeF N-terminal domain containing 3), CTC-260F20.3 and APOA1BP; RNA sequencing and microarray studies indicate that Y18D10A.3 is affected by let-418, chd-3, mir-34, daf-12, daf-16, dpy-21, pgl-1, pgl-3, glh-4, glh-1, and lin-35; microarray and RNA sequencing studies indicate that Y18D10A.3 is affected by Aldicarb, Rotenone, and Atrazine.
Y19D10A.16 is an ortholog of human GALM (galactose mutarotase); Y19D10A.16 is predicted to have carbohydrate binding activity and isomerase activity, based on protein domain information.
cht-4 is an ortholog of human OVGP1 (oviductal glycoprotein 1); cht-4 is predicted to have chitin binding activity, based on protein domain information.

set-21 encodes a putative histone H3 lysine-9 methyltransferase that  postpones polyglutamine aggregation in vivo, and that is predicted to  function in transcriptional repression; SET-21 has no non-nematode  orthologs, but is paralogous to SET-6, SET-15, and SET-32; SET-21  protein is specifically cleaved by CED-3, both in a genomic expression  screen and in an in vitro assay; set-21(RNAi) has no obvious phenotype  other than premature aggregation of transgenic Q33/Q35-YFP.

Y24D9A.8 is orthologous to the human gene Transaldolase 1 (TALDO1), a key enzyme in the pentose phosphate pathway, which provides ribose-5-phosphate for nucleic acid synthesis and NADPH for lipid biosynthesis.

Y37B11A.2 is an ortholog of human REV3L (REV3 like, DNA directed polymerase zeta catalytic subunit); Y37B11A.2 is predicted to have 3'-5' exonuclease activity, DNA-directed DNA polymerase activity, nucleic acid binding activity, and nucleotide binding activity, based on protein domain information.

Category 3: Neuronal function: synaptic function: neurotransmitter metabolism
Description: unc-25 encodes the C. elegans ortholog of the GABA neurotransmitter biosynthetic enzyme, glutamic acid decarboxylase (GAD); unc-25 activity is required for GABA synthesis and thus for normal synaptic transmission and GABA-mediated behaviors; UNC-25 is expressed specifically in the 26 GABAergic neurons as soon as they are generated and localizes to cell bodies, axonal branches, and synaptic regions, including some localization to synaptic vesicles; in the 19 type D GABAergic neurons, unc-25 expression is positively regulated by the UNC-30 homeodomain transcription factor, which binds to the unc-25 promoter in a sequence-specific manner.

ugt-45 is an ortholog of human UGT3A2 (UDP glycosyltransferase family 3 member A2) and UGT3A1 (UDP glycosyltransferase family 3 member A1); ugt-45 is predicted to have transferase activity, transferring hexosyl groups, based on protein domain information.

Y37E3.17 encodes a putative mitochondrial dimethylglycine dehydrogenase  orthologous to human DMGDH; studies indicate that the elegans dehydrogenase is a phosphorylcholine (PCho)-modified protein; P-Cho modification of proteins seems to play a developmental role in nematodes, as interfering with it, causes viability and fertility defects.

Category 2: Transcription: general machinery: RNA Pol II
Category 3: Transcription: general machinery: RNA Pol II: subunit
Description: Y37E3.3 encodes the C. elegans ortholog of the RNA polymerase II Rbp10 subunit; loss of Y37E3.3 activity via large-scale RNAi results in early embryonic lethality.
prdx-6 is an ortholog of human PRDX6 (peroxiredoxin 6); prdx-6 is predicted to have peroxiredoxin activity, based on protein domain information.

pnc-1 encodes, by alternative splicing, two isoforms of a putative  pyrazinamidase/nicotinamidase, orthologous to budding yeast Pnc1p, that  is required for normal lifespan; PNC-1 is paralogous to Y57G11C.47;  because its overexpression increases survival during oxidative stress,  PNC-1 may be required for oxidative resistance in vivo; pnc-1(RNAi)  animals are abnormally short-lived.

hphd-1 is an ortholog of human ADHFE1 (alcohol dehydrogenase, iron containing 1); hphd-1 is predicted to have metal ion binding activity and oxidoreductase activity, based on protein domain information; hphd-1 is expressed in the pharynx, anal depressor muscle, hypodermis, reproductive system, intestine, and the body wall musculature.
Y38F2AR.12 is an ortholog of human OPLAH (5-oxoprolinase (ATP-hydrolysing)); Y38F2AR.12 is predicted to have catalytic activity, based on protein domain information.

tgt-2 is an ortholog of human QTRTD1; tgt-2 is predicted to have transferase activity, transferring pentosyl groups, based on protein domain information; tgt-2 is expressed in the nervous system and the intestine.
gly-5 encodes a UDP-GalNAc:polypeptide N-acetylgalactosaminyltransferase; GLY-5 isoforms exhibit UDP-GalNAc:polypeptide N-acetylgalactosaminyltransferase activity in vitro.

dot-1.1 is an ortholog of human DOT1L (DOT1 like histone lysine methyltransferase); dot-1.1 is predicted to have histone methyltransferase activity (H3-K79 specific), based on protein domain information.

ugt-31 is an ortholog of human UGT3A2 (UDP glycosyltransferase family 3 member A2) and UGT3A1 (UDP glycosyltransferase family 3 member A1); ugt-31 is predicted to have transferase activity, transferring hexosyl groups, based on protein domain information.
Y41D4A.6 is an ortholog of human QRSL1 (glutaminyl-tRNA synthase (glutamine-hydrolyzing)-like 1); Y41D4A.6 is predicted to have amidase activity, based on protein domain information.
set-23 encodes, by alternative splicing, one isoform of a putative  histone H3 lysine-9 methyltransferase orthologous to human SETMAR  (OMIM:609834); set-23(n4496) has an embryonic lethal phenotype.
mvk-1 encodes an ortholog of the human gene MEVALONATE KINASE (MVK), which when mutated leads to mevalonicaciduria (OMIM:251170).

Y43F8B.19 is an ortholog of human P4HTM (prolyl 4-hydroxylase, transmembrane); Y43F8B.19 is predicted to have L-ascorbic acid binding activity, iron ion binding activity, and oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen, based on protein domain information.
gst-10 encodes a glutathione S-transferase with similarity to the pi class of human glutathione S-transferases; GST-10 catalyzes the conjugation of glutathione to 4-hydroxynonenal in vitro.

spds-1 encodes a spermidine synthase ortholog coexpressed in intestinal cells with smd-1 and odc-1; spds-1, smd-1 and odc-1, on the basis of orthology, are expected to be required for spermidine synthesis; a loss-of-function mutation of odc-1 is lethal; the spds-1 promoter has GATA- and initiator-(Inr)-like-elements that are conserved with its C. briggsae ortholog, and that are also found in the C. elegans and C. briggsae smd-1 promoters; the Inr-like-element of spds-1 is not its main transcriptional start site; unlike other metazoa, C. elegans lacks a spermine synthase ortholog.
cox-10 is orthologous to the human gene COX10 (YEAST) HOMOLOG, CYTOCHROME C OXIDASE ASSEMBLY PROTEIN (HEME A: FARNESYLTRANSFERASE) (COX10; OMIM:602125), which when mutated leads to disease.
gsy-1 is orthologous to the human gene GLYCOGEN SYNTHASE 1 (GYS1; OMIM:138570); deficiencies of GYS1 may be associated with susceptibility to type 2 diabetes.
gly-7 encodes an N-acetylgalactosaminyltransferase that exhibits activity when expressed in COS7 cells.

gly-9 is an ortholog of members of the human GALNT (Polypeptide N-acetylgalactosaminyltransferases) family including GALNT6; RNA sequencing and microarray studies indicate that gly-9 is affected by lin-39, lin-35, clk-1, tcer-1, cox-5B, jmjd-3.1, jmjd-1.2, hsf-1, emb-4, sma-2, sma-4, and daf-16; RNA sequencing studies indicate that gly-9 is affected by Zidovudine; RNA sequencing studies indicate that gly-9 is enriched in the EMS and intestine.

Y47D3A.29 encodes the catalytic subunit of DNA polymerase alpha; large-scale RNAi screens indicate that Y47D3A.29 activity is essential for embryogenesis and required specifically for normal pronuclear migration, as well as normal nuclear position and cell division timing in early blastomeres.
pcaf-1 encodes the sole C. elegans PCAF/GCN5-like histone acetyltransferase.

Category 2: Transcription: general machinery: RNA Pol III
Category 3: Transcription: general machinery: RNA Pol III
Description: Y47G6A.9 is an ortholog of human POLR3GL (RNA polymerase III subunit G like) and POLR3G (RNA polymerase III subunit G); Y47G6A.9 is predicted to have DNA-directed 5'-3' RNA polymerase activity, based on protein domain information.

Y48B6A.13 is an ortholog of human MVD (mevalonate diphosphate decarboxylase); Y48B6A.13 is predicted to have ATP binding activity and diphosphomevalonate decarboxylase activity, based on protein domain information.

Category 2: Transcription: general machinery: RNA Pol I
Category 3: Transcription: general machinery: RNA Pol I: subunit
Description: rpoa-1 is an ortholog of human POLR1A (RNA polymerase I subunit A); rpoa-1 is predicted to have DNA binding activity, DNA-directed 5'-3' RNA polymerase activity, and zinc ion binding activity, based on protein domain information.

Y48G10A.1 is an ortholog of human ESD (esterase D); Y48G10A.1 is predicted to have S-formylglutathione hydrolase activity, based on protein domain information; Y48G10A.1 is expressed in the nervous system, intestine, and the rectal gland cell.
Y48G8AL.15 is an ortholog of members of the human NME (NME/NM23) family including NME4; Y48G8AL.15 is predicted to have nucleoside diphosphate kinase activity, based on protein domain information.

Y48G8AL.5 is an ortholog of human Nsun2 (NOP2/Sun RNA methyltransferase family member 2); Y48G8AL.5 is predicted to have tRNA (cytosine-5-)-methyltransferase activity, based on protein domain information.

ppk-2 encodes a Type II phosphatidylinositol-4-phosphate kinase (PIP4K) that is one of three C. elegans PIP kinase homologs; PPK-2 is predicted to catalyze the phosphorylation of phosphatidylinositol-5-phosphate (PIP) on the 4-OH position to generate PI(4,5)P2; a deletion allele of ppk-2 is viable and does not affect PIP2 levels, suggesting that PPK-2 is not essential for PIP2 production.

ugt-29 is an ortholog of human UGT3A2 (UDP glycosyltransferase family 3 member A2) and UGT3A1 (UDP glycosyltransferase family 3 member A1); ugt-29 is predicted to have transferase activity, transferring hexosyl groups, based on protein domain information; ugt-29 is expressed in the pharynx, tail, intestine, and the vulval muscle.

sqv-6 encodes a xylosyltransferase, active in cell culture, that is required for cytokinesis of one-cell embryos and for vulval morphogenesis; SQV-6 is predicted to begin the synthesis of glycosaminoglycans by adding xylose to their protein cores; the common requirement for SQV-6 in both cytokinesis and morphogenesis may be to promote filling an extracellular space with hygroscopic proteoglycans (either in the eggshell, or underneath the L4 cuticle), which in turn may cause the space to fill with fluid.

Y50D4C.6 is an ortholog of human ADO (2-aminoethanethiol dioxygenase); Y50D4C.6 is predicted to have oxidoreductase activity, acting on single donors with incorporation of molecular oxygen, incorporation of two atoms of oxygen, based on protein domain information.

hpo-29 is an ortholog of human NAA16 (N(alpha)-acetyltransferase 16, NatA auxiliary subunit) and NAA15 (N(alpha)-acetyltransferase 15, NatA auxiliary subunit); hpo-29 is expressed in the anal depressor muscle, nervous system, and the body wall musculature.
Y51H4A.7 is an ortholog of human UROC1 (urocanate hydratase 1); Y51H4A.7 is predicted to have urocanate hydratase activity, based on protein domain information.

Microarray and RNA sequencing studies indicate that Y51H7C.9 is affected by nhr-114, nhr-62, eat-2, clk-1, csr-1, pgl-1, pgl-3, glh-4, glh-1, daf-2, npr-1, jmjd-3.1, jmjd-1.2, lsm-1, set-25, met-2, alg-1, isp-1, and nuo-6; microarray and RNA sequencing studies indicate that Y51H7C.9 is affected by Methylmercuric chloride, Manganese chloride, D-glucose, Atrazine, Paraquat, Colistin, Allantoin, and Octopamine; RNA sequencing studies indicate that Y51H7C.9 is enriched in the male and intestine.

Y53F4B.13 is an ortholog of human CMTR1 (cap methyltransferase 1); Y53F4B.13 is predicted to have mRNA (nucleoside-2'-O-)-methyltransferase activity and nucleic acid binding activity, based on protein domain information.
Y53F4B.3 is an ortholog of human POLE4 (DNA polymerase epsilon 4, accessory subunit); Y53F4B.3 is predicted to have protein heterodimerization activity, based on protein domain information.
Y53G8B.1 is an ortholog of human GstZ1 (glutathione S-transferase zeta 1); Y53G8B.1 is predicted to have catalytic activity, based on protein domain information.

Y54E10BR.1 is an ortholog of human PIGN (phosphatidylinositol glycan anchor biosynthesis class N); Y54E10BR.1 is involved in embryo development and nematode larval development;  PIGN has a large loop between the first and second transmembrane domains that contains three conserved motifs present in phosphodiesterases, nucleotide pyrophosphatases, and sulfatases, each of which is believed to be important for the PIGN catalytic activity in the EtNP transferase reaction; the mutations strongly (H263A in motif 3) or moderately (H218A in motif 2) affect the GPI synthesis activity of PIGN as determined by the surface expression of CD59 (GPI-AP) in PIGN-knockout HEK293 cells; PIGN-1/PIGN has a non-canonical function in protein quality control preventing protein aggregation within the ER in C. elegans and in mammalian cells; although PIGN was originally identified as an enzyme involved in glycosylphosphatidylinositol (GPI)-anchor biosynthesis, the function of PIGN-1/PIGN in protein quality control is independent of its enzymatic activities.

Category 2: Transcription: general machinery: RNA Pol II
Category 3: Transcription: general machinery: RNA Pol II: subunit
Description: rpb-7 is an ortholog of human POLR2G (RNA polymerase II subunit G); rpb-7 is predicted to have nucleic acid binding activity, based on protein domain information.

ctl-3 encodes one of three C. elegans catalases; CTL-3 is predicted to function as an antioxidant enzyme that protects cells from reactive oxygen species; a ctl-3 promoter gfp fusion construct is expressed in pharyngeal muscles and neuronal cell bodies; loss of ctl-3 activity via RNAi results in no obvious abnormalities.

nprt-1 is an ortholog of human NAPRT (nicotinate phosphoribosyltransferase); nprt-1 is predicted to have nicotinate-nucleotide diphosphorylase (carboxylating) activity, based on protein domain information; nprt-1 is expressed in the nervous system, reproductive system, and the intestine.

hel-308 encodes a putative DNA helicase orthologous to human HELQ and Drosophila MUS301/SPN-C/CG7972-PA; Drosophila MUS301 is required for normal resistance to nitrogen mustard (HN2) and to the crosslinking agent cisplatin, and is probably also required for repair of meiotic double-stranded DNA breaks; human HELQ is a single-stranded DNA-dependent ATPase and DNA helicase, and archaeal Hel308 (Mth810) may act at stalled replication forks by displacing lagging strands; HEL-308, HELQ, and CG7972-PA are paralogous to the N-terminal DNA helicase domains of human DNA POLYMERASE THETA (POLQ, OMIM:604419), Drosophila MUS308, and a putative C. elegans POLQ ortholog, encoded by polq-1; HEL-308, HELQ, and CG7972-PA belong to the superfamily II of DNA and RNA helicases; HEL-308 is probably, like MUS301, required for recombinational repair of cross-linkage or double-stranded breaks in DNA; biochemically, HEL-308 may unwind regions of cross-linked DNA before their repair by other proteins (such as POLQ), or resolve Holliday junctions after homologous recombination (as is done by the archaeal homolog Hjm).
faah-4 is an ortholog of human FAAH (fatty acid amide hydrolase); faah-4 is predicted to have amidase activity, based on protein domain information.
The nft-1 gene encodes an ortholog of human FHIT, which when mutated is associated with head and neck cancers (OMIM:601153).
faah-5 is an ortholog of human FAAH (fatty acid amide hydrolase); faah-5 is predicted to have amidase activity, based on protein domain information.

polg-1 encodes the C. elegans ortholog of human mitochondrial DNA polymerase gamma (POLG; OMIM:174763); polg-1 is required for normal levels of mitochondrial DNA during development, particularly during germ line development in late larval and adult stages;  polg-1 is also required for normal brood sizes and adult lifespan.

Y57G11C.3 encodes the C. elegans 6-phosphogluconolactonase (6PGL) ortholog; by homology, the product of Y57G11C.3 is predicted to catalyze the second reaction of the oxidative branch of the pentose-phosphate pathway in which 6-phosphogluconolactone is converted to 6-phosphogluconate.
pnc-2 encodes a pyrazinamidase/nicotinamidase, orthologous to budding yeast Pnc1p and paralogous to PNC-1.

mpst-5 is an ortholog of human tst (thiosulfate sulfurtransferase) and MPST (mercaptopyruvate sulfurtransferase); microarray, RNA sequencing, and proteomic studies indicate that mpst-5 is affected by atx-3, age-1, hlh-30, gld-2, hsf-1, mafr-1, glp-1, pgl-1, pgl-3, glh-4, and glh-1; RNA sequencing and microarray studies indicate that mpst-5 is affected by Ethanol and Methylmercuric chloride.

mpst-6 is an ortholog of human tst (thiosulfate sulfurtransferase) and MPST (mercaptopyruvate sulfurtransferase); microarray, RNA sequencing, and proteomic studies indicate that mpst-6 is affected by spe-44, gld-2, clk-1, jmjd-3.1, hsf-1, glp-1, pgl-1, pgl-3, glh-4, glh-1, dpy-9, dpy-10, osm-8, aak-2, his-24, hpl-1, hpl-2, isp-1, and nuo-6; microarray and RNA sequencing studies indicate that mpst-6 is affected by Heme, Ethanol, Quercetin, Humic substances, single-walled carbon nanotubes, Paraquat, Colistin, adsorbable organic bromine compounds, and Triclosan.

fars-2 is an ortholog of human FARS2 (phenylalanyl-tRNA synthetase 2, mitochondrial); fars-2 is predicted to have ATP binding activity, phenylalanine-tRNA ligase activity, and tRNA binding activity, based on protein domain information.

algn-7 is an ortholog of human DPAGT1 (dolichyl-phosphate N-acetylglucosaminephosphotransferase 1); algn-7 is predicted to have UDP-N-acetylglucosamine-dolichyl-phosphate N-acetylglucosaminephosphotransferase activity and phospho-N-acetylmuramoyl-pentapeptide-transferase activity, based on protein domain information.

Y62E10A.13 is an ortholog of human PSPH (phosphoserine phosphatase); Y62E10A.13 is predicted to have phosphoserine phosphatase activity, based on protein domain information; Y62E10A.13 is expressed in the head and the intestine.
agt-1 encodes an ortholog of the DNA repair enzyme O6-Alkylguanine DNA-alkyltransferase (AGT).
Y62E10A.6 is an ortholog of human FDXR (ferredoxin reductase); Y62E10A.6 is predicted to have oxidoreductase activity, based on protein domain information.
Y65B4A.8 is an ortholog of human COASY (Coenzyme A synthase); Y65B4A.8 is predicted to have ATP binding activity and dephospho-CoA kinase activity, based on protein domain information.

nars-2 is an ortholog of human NARS2 (asparaginyl-tRNA synthetase 2, mitochondrial (putative)); nars-2 is predicted to have aminoacyl-tRNA ligase activity and nucleotide binding activity, based on protein domain information.
Y66D12A.7 is an ortholog of human GATC (glutamyl-tRNA amidotransferase subunit C) and AL021546.6; Y66D12A.7 is expressed in the hypodermis and the tail.

dpm-1 encodes a putative catalytic subunit of dolichol phosphate  mannosyltransferase, orthologous to budding yeast and human DPM1  (OMIM:603503, mutated in congenital disorder of glycosylation type Ie);  in mass RNAi assays, DPM-1 is required for embryonic viability and  proper cortical motion in the early embryo.

mca-3 encodes one of three C. elegans plasma membrane Ca2+ ATPases (PMCAs); by homology, MCA-3 is predicted to function as a molecular pump that couples ATP hydrolysis to extrusion of cytosolic Ca2+; mca-3 activity is required for coelomoycte endocytosis, normal coordinated locomotion, and embryonic and larval development; in regulating endocytosis, MCA-3 is required specifically in the early stages for recruitment of the endocytic machinery to the plasma membrane; an mca-3::gfp reporter is expressed from embryogenesis through adulthood and seen in body wall muscle, the nervous system, intestine, and coelomocytes; in coelomocytes, an MCA-3::GFP fusion protein localizes to the plasma membrane.

daao-1 encodes a D-amino acid oxidase (DAAO); recombinant DAOO-1 has DAAO activity on neutral and basic D-amino acid substrates (e.g., D-alanine or D-methionine, and D-arginine), with highest catalytic efficiency on D-arginine; since the C-terminal residues of DAAO-1 match the PTS1 consensus sequence, DAAO-1 is predicted to be peroxisomal.
acsd-1 is an ortholog of human ACMSD (aminocarboxymuconate semialdehyde decarboxylase); acsd-1 is predicted to have hydrolase activity, based on protein domain information.

parp-1 (formerly known as pme-1) encodes a poly(ADP-ribose) polymerase (PARP) orthologous to human PARP1 (OMIM:173870); PARP-1 has two N-terminal zinc fingers that probably bind DNA, and a C-terminal catalytic domain; PARP-1 exhibits poly(ADP-ribose) activity in vitro, which is blocked by mammalian PARP inhibitors; since these inhibitors also cause embryonic lethality in worms exposed to ionizing radiation, PARP-1 is likely to be required in vivo for repairing broken DNA.
gst-43 is an ortholog of human GstZ1 (glutathione S-transferase zeta 1); gst-43 is predicted to have catalytic activity, based on protein domain information.
Y71F9B.9 is an ortholog of human CRYL1 (crystallin lambda 1); Y71F9B.9 is predicted to have 3-hydroxyacyl-CoA dehydrogenase activity, based on protein domain information.

pghm-1 is an ortholog of human PAM (peptidylglycine alpha-amidating monooxygenase); pghm-1 is predicted to have copper ion binding activity and oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen, reduced ascorbate as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen, based on protein domain information.

pho-9 is an ortholog of human ACP2 (acid phosphatase 2, lysosomal), ACPT (acid phosphatase, testicular) and ACPP (acid phosphatase, prostate); microarray and RNA sequencing studies indicate that pho-9 is affected by Heme, Ethanol, Rotenone, Tunicamycin, D-glucopyranose, 4-bromodiphenyl ether, Chlorpyrifos, Diazinon, Quercetin, Humic substances, Colistin, Dafa#1, and adsorbable organic bromine compounds; tiling array, RNA sequencing, and microarray studies indicate that pho-9 is enriched in the intestine and body wall musculature and in the PVD, OLL, and ASER neurons.

Y71H2AM.2 is an ortholog of human TMEM55A (transmembrane protein 55A) and TMEM55B (transmembrane protein 55B); Y71H2AM.2 is predicted to have phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate 4-phosphatase activity, based on protein domain information.

Y71H2AM.6 is an ortholog of human Ppcs (phosphopantothenoylcysteine synthetase); microarray, tiling array, and RNA sequencing studies indicate that Y71H2AM.6 is affected by cyc-1, lin-15B, daf-12, daf-16, cox-5B, jmjd-3.1, jmjd-1.2, slr-2, fbf-1, cdk-4, cyd-1, and nuo-6; microarray studies indicate that Y71H2AM.6 is affected by Hydrolyzable Tannins and Allantoin; RNA sequencing and microarray studies indicate that Y71H2AM.6 is enriched in the germ line and intestine and in neurons including the GABAergic neurons.

Microarray and RNA sequencing studies indicate that Y73B3A.3 is affected by cyc-1, drh-3, htz-1, daf-16, hsf-1, emb-4, hrde-1, sma-2, sma-4, smg-2, ain-1, ain-2, dpy-9, dpy-10, and osm-8; RNA sequencing and microarray studies indicate that Y73B3A.3 is affected by Mianserin and Cadmium; tiling array and RNA sequencing studies indicate that Y73B3A.3 is enriched in the germline precursor cell and in the AVE neurons.

Category 3: Neuronal function: synaptic function: neurotransmitter metabolism
Description: tyr-6 is orthologous to the human gene tyrosinase (TYR), which is involved in the conversion of tyrosine to melanin.

acp-7 is an ortholog of human ACPT (acid phosphatase, testicular), ACPP (acid phosphatase, prostate) and ACP2 (acid phosphatase 2, lysosomal); microarray, RNA sequencing, and tiling array studies indicate that acp-7 is affected by cid-1, rsr-2, daf-2, daf-16, hpk-1, npr-1, jmjd-3.1, jmjd-1.2, let-418, dpy-21, mir-34, daf-12, hrde-1, morc-1, ash-2, crh-1, tax-6, isp-1, nuo-6, and pmk-1; RNA sequencing and microarray studies indicate that acp-7 is affected by Rotenone, Bisphenol A, Diazinon, Quercetin, Colistin, Dafa#1, and Sirolimus; tiling array and RNA sequencing studies indicate that acp-7 is enriched in the excretory cell, arcade cell, and pharyngeal-intestinal valve cell and in the PVD and OLL neurons.

Y73B6BL.29 is an ortholog of human PUSL1 (pseudouridylate synthase-like 1); Y73B6BL.29 is predicted to have RNA binding activity and pseudouridine synthase activity, based on protein domain information.
bre-4 encodes a beta-1,4-N-acetylgalactosaminyltransferase that is required for the toxicity of Bacillus thuringiensis Cry5B.
Y75B8A.24 is an ortholog of human PI4KA (phosphatidylinositol 4-kinase alpha); Y75B8A.24 is predicted to have kinase activity, based on protein domain information.
gly-11 is an ortholog of human GALNT11 (polypeptide N-acetylgalactosaminyltransferase 11); gly-11 is expressed in the mc3, mc1, pm7, pm6, pm4, pm3, pm8, hypodermis, and the excretory cell.

hxk-3 is an ortholog of human HK3 (hexokinase 3), GCK (glucokinase), HKDC1 (hexokinase domain containing 1), HK1 (hexokinase 1) and HK2 (hexokinase 2); hxk-3 is predicted to have ATP binding activity and hexokinase activity, based on protein domain information.

Category 2: Transcription: general machinery: RNA Pol III
Category 3: Transcription: general machinery: RNA Pol III
Description: rpc-11 is an ortholog of human POLR3K (RNA polymerase III subunit K); rpc-11 is predicted to have nucleic acid binding activity, based on protein domain information.
wrs-1 encodes a predicted tryptophanyl-tRNA synthetase that affects fertility, embryonic viability, growth, and locomotion

glp-4 is an ortholog of human VARS (valyl-tRNA synthetase) and VARS2 (valyl-tRNA synthetase 2, mitochondrial); glp-4 is predicted to have ATP binding activity, aminoacyl-tRNA editing activity, and valine-tRNA ligase activity, based on protein domain information.

gpi-1 encodes two isoforms of a putative glucose 6-phosphate isomerase orthologous to human GPI (OMIM:172400, mutated in chronic hemolytic anemia); gpi-1 is required both for embryonic viability and (paradoxically) for normally short lifespan; gpi-1 is expressed in neurons and intestine.
The Y92H12BL.5 gene encodes a NUDIX hydrolase.

Y94H6A.7 is an ortholog of human Acp1 (acid phosphatase 1, soluble); Y94H6A.7 is predicted to have acid phosphatase activity and non-membrane spanning protein tyrosine phosphatase activity, based on protein domain information.
pde-6 encodes a 3'-5'-cAMP phosphodiesterase most similar to the mammalian PDE8 family of enzymes; in C. elegans, PDE-6 activity is required for negative regulation of oocyte maturation.

abhd-12 is an ortholog of human ABHD12 (abhydrolase domain containing 12) and ABHD12B (abhydrolase domain containing 12B); tiling array, RNA sequencing, and microarray studies indicate that abhd-12 is affected by daf-12, tatn-1, htz-1, pgl-1, pgl-3, glh-4, glh-1, sir-2.1, fbf-1, and gld-1; microarray studies indicate that abhd-12 is affected by Progesterone, Atrazine, and Fluoranthene; tiling array, RNA sequencing, and microarray studies indicate that abhd-12 is enriched in the germ line and in neurons.
natb-1 is an ortholog of human NAA20 (N(alpha)-acetyltransferase 20, NatB catalytic subunit); natb-1 is predicted to have N-acetyltransferase activity, based on protein domain information.

Y97E10AR.2 is an ortholog of human GGT2 (gamma-glutamyltransferase 2), GGT5 (gamma-glutamyltransferase 5) and GGT1 (gamma-glutamyltransferase 1); Y97E10AR.2 is predicted to have glutathione hydrolase activity, based on protein domain information; Y97E10AR.2 is expressed in the intestine, body wall musculature, and the head neurons.

Category 2: Transcription: general machinery: RNA Pol II
Category 3: Transcription: general machinery: RNA Pol II: subunit
Description: rpb-9 is an ortholog of human POLR2I (RNA polymerase II subunit I); rpb-9 is predicted to have nucleic acid binding activity and zinc ion binding activity, based on protein domain information.
Y9C9A.16 is an ortholog of human RP11-96O20.4 and SQRDL (sulfide quinone reductase-like (yeast)); Y9C9A.16 is predicted to have oxidoreductase activity, based on protein domain information.
ZC250.2 is an ortholog of human B3GLCT (beta 3-glucosyltransferase); ZC250.2 is predicted to have transferase activity, transferring glycosyl groups, based on protein domain information.
cbs-1 encodes an ortholog of human CYSTATHIONINE-BETA-SYNTHASE (CBS), which when mutated leads to homocystinuria (OMIM:236200).
hap-1 is an ortholog of human ITPA (inosine triphosphatase); hap-1 is predicted to have nucleoside-triphosphate diphosphatase activity, based on protein domain information.

mans-4 is an ortholog of human MAN1B1 (mannosidase, alpha1B, member 1); mans-4 is involved in embryo development; mans-4 has a calcium ion dependent mannosyl-oligosaccharide 1,2-alpha-mannosidase activity ('ER-mannosidase'), based on enzymatic assay, with Man8GlcNAc2 (isomer B) as a final product.

Category 3: Signaling: heteromeric G protein: guanylyl cyclase
Description: gcy-14 encodes a transmembrane guanylyl cyclase; gcy-14 mutant animals are sodium and lithium chemotaxis defective; a gcy-14::gfp reporter fusion is expressed predominantly in the ASE(L) chemosensory neuron, with some fainter expression seen in AWC and PVT.

ers-2 encodes a predicted mitochondrial glutamyl-tRNA synthetase (GluRS), a class I aminoacyl-tRNA synthetase that catalyzes the attachment of glutamate to its cognate tRNA and is thus required for protein biosynthesis; ERS-2 contains, at its C-terminus, six tandemly repeated WHEP-TRS domains that have been predicted to function as general RNA-binding domains that may act as cis tRNA-binding cofactors.

ZC434.8 is an ortholog of human CKMT2 (creatine kinase, mitochondrial 2), CKM (creatine kinase, M-type), CKB (creatine kinase B) and CKMT1B (creatine kinase, mitochondrial 1B); ZC434.8 is predicted to have kinase activity, based on protein domain information.

ugt-6 is an ortholog of human UGT3A2 (UDP glycosyltransferase family 3 member A2) and UGT3A1 (UDP glycosyltransferase family 3 member A1); ugt-6 is predicted to have transferase activity, transferring hexosyl groups, based on protein domain information.

ugt-4 is an ortholog of human UGT3A2 (UDP glycosyltransferase family 3 member A2) and UGT3A1 (UDP glycosyltransferase family 3 member A1); ugt-4 is predicted to have transferase activity, transferring hexosyl groups, based on protein domain information.
ZC513.5 is an ortholog of human ALG12 (ALG12, alpha-1,6-mannosyltransferase); ZC513.5 is predicted to have transferase activity, transferring glycosyl groups, based on protein domain information.

mmcm-1 encodes an ortholog of human methylmalonyl-CoA mutase (MUT); MMCM-1 enzyme, in vitro,  kinetically resembles its human ortholog; mmcm-1 deletion mutants  incorporate abnormally low levels of 1-[(14)C]-propionate into proteins;  mmcm-1(RNAi) and mmcm-1 deletion mutant animals excrete abnormally high  levels of methylmalonic acid into their culture medium when challenged  with propionic acid; mmcm-1, in a lentiviral transgene, can partially  rescue the mutant phenotype of human mut(o) fibroblasts; these data are  consistent with the hypothesis that MMCM-1 participates in the conversion  of propionyl-CoA to succinyl-CoA.
ZK1058.3 is orthologous to the human gene UNNAMED PROTEIN PRODUCT (GALT; OMIM:606999), which when mutated leads to disease.
The pmr-1 gene encodes a Golgi P-type ATPase Ca^2+/Mn^2+-pump; mutations in its human ortholog, ATP2C1, cause Hailey-Hailey disease (OMIM:169600).

aco-1 encodes an aconitase that is homologous to mammalian iron regulatory protein-1 (IRP1); aco-1 activity is required for normal brood sizes and, under iron stress conditions, for normal lifespan and L4-to-adult growth rates; ACO-1 physically interacts with GEX-3; like IRP1, ACO-1 has aconitase activity and is post-translationally regulated by iron, but, unlike IRP1, it lacks RNA-binding activity; aco-1 mRNA levels appear to decrease in response to iron treatment; an ACO-1::GFP fusion protein exhibits cytosolic expression in the hypodermal seam cells and the intestine.

Category 3: Signaling: heteromeric G protein: guanylyl cyclase
Description: gcy-9 is an ortholog of human NPR1 (natriuretic peptide receptor 1) and NPR2 (natriuretic peptide receptor 2); gcy-9 is predicted to have ATP binding activity, guanylate cyclase activity, and protein kinase activity, based on protein domain information; gcy-9 is expressed in certain sensory neurons.

lars-2 encodes the ortholog of human leucyl amino-acyl tRNA synthetase (LARS); in C. elegans, lars-2 is required for normal mitochondrial structure and function, and acts downstream of daf-2 to control lifespan; lars-2 mutants show swollen, disorganized and sometimes fused mitochondria, and live much longer than wild-type worms; a lars-2 GFP translation fusion gene was ubiquitously expressed, with prominent expression in body-wall muscle and neurons and with subcellular localization in the mitochondria; being a tRNA synthetase that charges mitochondrial tRNAs for translation, lars-2 is predicted to specifically compromise mitochondrial electron transport and ATP synthesis, through it's effects on mitochrondrially encoded genes.

ZK563.7 is an ortholog of human CANT1 (calcium activated nucleotidase 1); ZK563.7 is predicted to have calcium ion binding activity and nucleoside-diphosphatase activity, based on protein domain information.
ZK632.4 is orthologous to the human gene PHOSPHOMANNOSE ISOMERASE (MPI; OMIM:154550), which when mutated leads to disease.

trxr-2 encodes a thioredoxin reductase; TRXR-2 exhibits catalytic activity in vitro, reducing the redox-active disulfide bond of thioredoxin; large-scale expression studies indicate that a trxr-2::gfp reporter fusion is expressed in the intestine and in neurons.

asna-1 encodes a putative membrane transporter that is required, non-cell-autonomously, for L1 larvae to proceed through development when fed, and is also required for normal insulin (DAF-28) secretion; the human ASNA1 ortholog stimulates insulin secretion in pancreatic beta cells, and can transgenically rescue asna-1 mutant C. elegans, suggesting that ASNA-1's function is conserved among metazoa; asna-1 mutants only progress to adulthood when rescued by maternal ASNA-1; without maternal rescue, asna-1 mutants eat food and endocytose nutrients normally, but nevertheless arrest growth as L1 larvae and localize DAF-16 to the nucleus as if food were absent; asna-1 is expressed in some sensory neurons, in insulin-producing intestinal cells, and in hypodermis; ASNA-1 positively regulates dauer exit in the same way that overexpression of the insulins DAF-28 or INS-4 does, and requires DAF-28 to do this efficiently; ASNA-1 has ATPase activity in vitro, and this activity is required for transgenic rescue of asna-1 mutations.

ZK673.2 is an ortholog of human AK3 (adenylate kinase 3) and AK4 (adenylate kinase 4); ZK673.2 is predicted to have ATP binding activity and nucleobase-containing compound kinase activity, based on protein domain information.
ZK697.8 is an ortholog of human TTR (transthyretin); ZK697.8 is predicted to have hydroxyisourate hydrolase activity, based on protein domain information.

Category 3: Neuronal function: synaptic function: neurotransmitter metabolism
Description: hdl-1 encodes a protein with similarity to aromatic amino acid and histidine decarboxylases; sequence comparisons indicate that HDL-1 is much larger than typical aromatic amino acid decarboxylases, containing extended N- and C-terminal domains not found in other pyridoxal-5'-phosphate-dependent decarboxylases.

gdh-1 encodes a glutamate dehydrogenase, required in mass RNAi assays for normal fertility and rapid growth, that is expressed in larval and adult pharynx, intestine, and rectal gland cells; GDH-1 is orthologous to human GLUD1 (OMIM:138130, mutated in hyperinsulinemic  hypoglycemia and hyperammonemia) and GLUD2 (OMIM:300144).

ogdh-2 is an ortholog of human DHTKD1 (dehydrogenase E1 and transketolase domain containing 1); ogdh-2 is predicted to have oxoglutarate dehydrogenase (succinyl-transferring) activity and thiamine pyrophosphate binding activity, based on protein domain information; ogdh-2 is expressed in the body wall musculature.

Category 2: Transcription: general machinery: RNA Pol II
Category 3: Transcription: general machinery: RNA Pol II: elongation
Description: elpc-3 is an ortholog of human Elp3 (elongator acetyltransferase complex subunit 3); elpc-3 is involved in embryonic morphogenesis, olfactory learning, oocyte development, spermatogenesis, tRNA wobble uridine modification, translation and vulval development; elpc-3 is predicted to have N-acetyltransferase activity and iron-sulfur cluster binding activity, based on protein domain information; elpc-3 is expressed in several tissues including the pharynx and the vulva.

pdp-1 is an ortholog of human PDP2 (pyruvate dehyrogenase phosphatase catalytic subunit 2) and Pdp1 (pyruvate dehyrogenase phosphatase catalytic subunit 1); pdp-1 is predicted to have protein serine/threonine phosphatase activity, based on protein domain information.

pstk-1 is an ortholog of human PSTK (phosphoseryl-tRNA kinase); microarray and RNA sequencing studies indicate that pstk-1 is affected by clk-1, let-418, chd-3, pgl-1, pgl-3, glh-4, glh-1, emb-4, sir-2.1, ain-2, mir-243, and isp-1; microarray and RNA sequencing studies indicate that pstk-1 is affected by Hydrogen sulfide, Rotenone, Atrazine, Colistin, Allantoin, and Sirolimus; RNA sequencing studies indicate that pstk-1 is enriched in the Z4, Z1, and germ line.

tpk-1 is an ortholog of human TPK1 (thiamin pyrophosphokinase 1); tpk-1 is predicted to have thiamine binding activity and thiamine diphosphokinase activity, based on protein domain information; tpk-1 is expressed in the pharyngeal muscle cell and the body wall musculature.

F42G8.10 is an ortholog of human NDUFB11 (NADH:ubiquinone oxidoreductase subunit B11); proteomic, RNA sequencing, and microarray studies indicate that F42G8.10 is affected by daf-2, gld-1, let-7, gas-1, daf-16, jmjd-3.1, jmjd-1.2, hsf-1, ifg-1, mir-34, emb-4, sir-2.1, and lin-35; microarray studies indicate that F42G8.10 is affected by Progesterone; proteomic and microarray studies indicate that F42G8.10 is enriched in the germ line and muscle cell and in neurons.
F44G4.2 is an ortholog of human NDUFB2 (NADH:ubiquinone oxidoreductase subunit B2); F44G4.2 is localized to the mitochondrion.
F45H10.3 is an ortholog of human NDUFA7 (NADH:ubiquinone oxidoreductase subunit A7); F45H10.3 is predicted to have NADH dehydrogenase (ubiquinone) activity, based on protein domain information.
The atp-6 gene resides on the mitochondrial chromosome, and encodes the protein ATP synthase subunit a; this is the C. elegans homolog of the MT-ATP6 mitochondrial membrane ATP synthase (Complex V).

The ctb-1 gene resides on the mitochondrial chromosome, and encodes the cytochrome b protein of mitochondrial complex III; mutation of ctb-1 suppresses the slow embryonic development of isp-1 mutants, while enhancing their paraquat resistance.

The ctc-3 gene resides on the mitochondrial chromosome, and encodes the protein cytochrome c oxidase subunit 3; cytochrome c oxidase is the component of the respiratory chain that catalyzes the reduction of oxygen to water; CTC-3 is one of the 3 subunits (1-3) that forms the functional core of the enzyme complex.

The ctc-2 gene resides on the mitochondrial chromosome, and encodes the protein cytochrome c oxidase subunit 2; cytochrome c oxidase is the component of the respiratory chain that catalyzes the reduction of oxygen to water; CTC-2 is one of the 3 subunits (1-3) that forms the functional core of the enzyme complex.

spe-5 encodes an ortholog of subunit B of the cytoplasmic (V1) domain of vacuolar proton-translocating ATPase (V-ATPase); spe-5 was identified in screens for mutations that result in defective spermatogenesis; defined by six cold-sensitive alleles, spe-5 is required for morphogenesis of the Golgi-derived fibrous body-membranous organelle (FB-MO) complex that is essential for the second, asymmetric meiotic division that produces four haploid spermatids; mutations of spe-5 suppress necrotic neurodegeneration; SPE-5 may also play a role in acidification of the FB-MO, a process known to occur during C. elegans spermatid formation.

vha-11 encodes, by alternative splicing, two isoforms of an ortholog of subunit C of the cytoplasmic (V1) domain of vacuolar proton-translocating ATPase (V-ATPase); VHA-11 is a predicted cytosolic stator (stalk) component; VHA-11 is found in dot-like structures around embryonic nuclei, with diffuse distribution in embryonic cytoplasm; in later embryos (comma stage onward), VHA-11 is found in gut granules (a type of lysosome, expected to require acidification); VHA-11 is predominantly expressed in the excretory cell and in intestinal cells in the adult; VHA-11 is required for ovulation and embryogenesis, since vha-11(RNAi) animals are sterile with polyploid, unmatured oocytes and dead progeny; VHA-11 is also required for normal formation of gut granules, since vha-11(RNAi) embryonic intestines fail to stain with acridine orange; glo-1 mutant intestines fail to show punctate VHA-11; vha-11 shares an operon with vha-3; transgenic vha-11 complements a null mutation of its S. cerevisiae ortholog, VMA5.

vha-3 and vha-2 encode an ortholog of subunit c of the membrane-bound (V0) domain of vacuolar proton-translocating ATPase (V-ATPase); the protein encoded by vha-2 and vha-3 (VHA-2/3) is identical; VHA-2/3 is a predicted V-ATPase transmembrane rotor component; VHA-1 and VHA-2/3 comprise a closely related family of subunit c co-orthologs, predicted to carry protons from the cytosol to a-subunits (VHA-5, VHA-6, VHA-7, or UNC-32) for transmembrane export; vha-3 shares an operon with vha-11; unlike its twin vha-2, the vha-3 gene is intronless; VHA-2/3 is dispensable for viability, since vha-2/3(RNAi) animals have mostly healthy progeny; vha-3 is expressed predominantly in the gastrointestinal and hypodermal cells, and weakly in the excretory cell.

Y51H1A.3 encodes the C. elegans ortholog of NDUFB8, an accessory subunit of the mitochondrial respiratory chain NADH:ubiquinone oxidoreductase (Complex I); large-scale RNAi screens indicate that Y51H1A.3 activity is required for embryonic and larval development, normal brood size, and molting.

Y53G8AL.2 is an ortholog of human NDUFA9 (NADH:ubiquinone oxidoreductase subunit A9); Y53G8AL.2 is expressed in the pharynx, anal depressor muscle, hypodermis, head, tail, reproductive system, intestine, excretory cell, and the body wall musculature.
nduf-5 encodes the C. elegans ortholog of the NDUFS5/15 kDa subunit of the mitochondrial NADH dehydrogenase (ubiquinone) complex (complex I).

Y54F10AM.5 is an ortholog of human NDUFA8 (NADH:ubiquinone oxidoreductase subunit A8); microarray, tiling array, and RNA sequencing studies indicate that Y54F10AM.5 is affected by cyc-1, daf-12, aak-2, crtc-1, cox-5B, jmjd-3.1, jmjd-1.2, hsf-1, mir-34, and gei-8; microarray and RNA sequencing studies indicate that Y54F10AM.5 is affected by Biotin, Rotenone, and Hydrolyzable Tannins; proteomic and RNA sequencing studies indicate that Y54F10AM.5 is enriched in the germ line and in the ASER and PLM neurons.

Y69A2AR.18 is an ortholog of human ATP5C1 (ATP synthase, H+ transporting, mitochondrial F1 complex, gamma polypeptide 1); Y69A2AR.18 is predicted to have proton-transporting ATP synthase activity, rotational mechanism, based on protein domain information; Y69A2AR.18 is expressed in the pharynx, anal depressor muscle, hypodermis, nervous system, tail, and the body wall musculature.

Y71H2AM.4 is an ortholog of human NDUFC2-KCTD14 (NDUFC2-KCTD14 readthrough) and NDUFC2 (NADH:ubiquinone oxidoreductase subunit C2); Y71H2AM.4 is predicted to have NADH dehydrogenase (ubiquinone) activity, based on protein domain information.

cox-6B is an ortholog of human COX6B1 (cytochrome c oxidase subunit 6B1) and COX6B2 (cytochrome c oxidase subunit 6B2); RNA sequencing, tiling array, and microarray studies indicate that cox-6B is affected by aak-2, daf-12, daf-16, npr-1, jmjd-3.1, jmjd-1.2, emb-4, and sir-2.1; RNA sequencing studies indicate that cox-6B is affected by Rotenone and D-glucose; RNA sequencing and microarray studies indicate that cox-6B is enriched in the intestine and male-specific tissues and in neurons including the NSM, AFD, and ASER neurons.

Y82E9BR.3 is an ortholog of human ATP5G1 (ATP synthase, H+ transporting, mitochondrial Fo complex subunit C1 (subunit 9)), ATP5G2 (ATP synthase, H+ transporting, mitochondrial Fo complex subunit C2 (subunit 9)) and ATP5G3 (ATP synthase, H+ transporting, mitochondrial Fo complex subunit C3 (subunit 9)); Y82E9BR.3 is predicted to have hydrogen ion transmembrane transporter activity, based on protein domain information.

lpd-5 is orthologous to the human gene NADH DEHYDROGENASE (UBIQUINONE) FE-S PROTEIN 4 (18KD) (NADH-COENZYME Q REDUCTASE) (NDUFS4; OMIM:602694), which when mutated leads to NADH:ubiquinone oxidoreductase (complex I) deficiency.

ggtb-1 is an ortholog of human RABGGTB (Rab geranylgeranyltransferase beta subunit); ggtb-1 is predicted to have catalytic activity, based on protein domain information; ggtb-1 is expressed in the pharyngeal muscle cell, nervous system, head, tail, intestine, body wall musculature, Eplpp, Ealaa, Earaa, and the Eprpp.

folt-1 encodes a folate transporter required for folate uptake; FOLT-1  is orthologous to the human folate transporter, SLC19A3 (Solute Carrier Family 19 (thiamine transporter), Member 3); folt-1 is required for proper germline function, oogenesis and sperm number in males, and for normal life-span; folt-1 mutants and folt-1(RNAi) animals show significantly lowered folate uptake; heterologously expressed FOLT-1 transports folate in vitro; FOLT-1 activity is acid-dependent, is sodium-independent, and is inhibited by folate derivatives, sulfasalazine, or anion transport inhibitors such as 4,4''-diisothio-cyanatostilbene-2,2''-disulphonic acid (DIDS); folt-1 is expressed in several tissues, including (most strongly) pharynx and posterior intestine, as well as head, body wall, vulva muscles, and gonad sheath cells.
afmd-1 is an ortholog of human AFMID (arylformamidase); afmd-1 is predicted to have hydrolase activity, based on protein domain information.
F31D4.9 is involved in mitochondrial electron transport, NADH to ubiquinone.

ucr-11 is an ortholog of human UQCR11 (ubiquinol-cytochrome c reductase, complex III subunit XI); ucr-11 is predicted to have ubiquinol-cytochrome-c reductase activity, based on protein domain information; ucr-11 is localized to the mitochondrion.

fgt-1 is an ortholog of members of the human SLC (Solute carriers) family including SLC2A14; fgt-1 is involved in glucose transport; fgt-1 is predicted to have transmembrane transporter activity, based on protein domain information; fgt-1 is expressed in the muscle cell, pharynx, hypodermis, nervous system, and the intestinal cell.

parg-2 (formerly known as pme-4) encodes a poly(ADP-ribose) glycohydrolase (PARG) orthologous to human PARG (OMIM:603501) and paralogous to PARG-1; PARG-2 exhibits poly(ADP-ribose) glycohydrolase activity in vitro, and is required in vivo for normal resistance to ionizing radiation; PARG-2 is primarily expressed in the cytoplasm of nerve cells in the head and tail, and also in embryos; neuronal expression of PARG-2 may reflect a requirement for PARG in preventing neurodegeneration like that seen in Drosophila.

hrg-1 encodes a transmembrane protein that is orthologous to vertebrate heme transporters; in C. elegans, hrg-1 functions to mediate heme homeostasis, likely by regulating intracellular heme availability from endosomal or lysosomal-like compartments; HRG-1  exhibits pH-dependent heme binding in vitro and when expressed in Xenopus oocytes,  can stimulate heme-dependent currents; an hrg-1::gfp promoter fusion is expressed  in the larval and adult intestine in response to heme deficiency; when expressed  in HEK293 cells, HRG-1 localizes primarily to endosomes and lysosome-related organelles;  HRG-1 function is likely conserved across species, as hrg-1 expression is able to  rescue developmental defects seen in zebrafish hrg-1 mutants.
Y39B6A.3 is an ortholog of human ISCA1 (iron-sulfur cluster assembly 1); Y39B6A.3 is predicted to have structural molecule activity, based on protein domain information.
Y39G8B.2 is an ortholog of members of the human AKR (Aldo-keto reductases) family including AKR1C2; Y39G8B.2 is predicted to have oxidoreductase activity, based on protein domain information.

bcmo-1 is an ortholog of human RPE65 (RPE65, retinoid isomerohydrolase), BCO2 (beta-carotene oxygenase 2) and BCO1 (beta-carotene oxygenase 1); bcmo-1 is predicted to have oxidoreductase activity, acting on single donors with incorporation of molecular oxygen, incorporation of two atoms of oxygen, based on protein domain information; bcmo-1 is expressed in the intestine.

rft-2 is an ortholog of human SLC52A2 (solute carrier family 52 member 2), SLC52A3 (solute carrier family 52 member 3) and SLC52A1 (solute carrier family 52 member 1); rft-2 exhibits riboflavin transmembrane transporter activity; rft-2 is expressed in the intestine.

rft-1 is an ortholog of human SLC52A2 (solute carrier family 52 member 2), SLC52A3 (solute carrier family 52 member 3) and SLC52A1 (solute carrier family 52 member 1); rft-1 is involved in embryo development; rft-1 exhibits riboflavin transmembrane transporter activity.
Y48E1B.3 is an ortholog of human PGGT1B (protein geranylgeranyltransferase type I subunit beta); Y48E1B.3 is predicted to have catalytic activity, based on protein domain information.
nsun-5 is an ortholog of human NSUN5 (NOP2/Sun domain 5); nsun-5 codes for a protein that methylates cytosine 2381 of 26S ribosomal RNA and thereby modulates lifespan and paraquat resistance.
Y56A3A.36 is an ortholog of human DOLK (dolichol kinase); RNA sequencing studies indicate that Y56A3A.36 is affected by prg-1, gld-2, and hsf-1.
ZC443.1 is an ortholog of members of the human AKR (Aldo-keto reductases) family including AKR1C1; ZC443.1 is predicted to have oxidoreductase activity, based on protein domain information.

hsd-3 is an ortholog of human SDR42E2 (short chain dehydrogenase/reductase family 42E, member 2), SDR42E1 (short chain dehydrogenase/reductase family 42E, member 1) and NSDHL (NAD(P) dependent steroid dehydrogenase-like); hsd-3 is predicted to have 3-beta-hydroxy-delta5-steroid dehydrogenase activity, based on protein domain information.
ZK973.11 is an ortholog of human TMX3 (thioredoxin related transmembrane protein 3); ZK973.11 is expressed in the nervous system and the intestine.

sir-2.4 is an ortholog of human Sirt6 (sirtuin 6); sir-2.4 is involved in P granule assembly and response to heat; sir-2.4 exhibits transcription factor binding activity and is predicted to have NAD+ binding activity, based on protein domain information; sir-2.4 is expressed in the head neurons, tail neurons, and the spermathecal-uterine valve cell; sir-2.4 is localized to the P granule, the cytoplasmic stress granule and the nuclear pore.

catp-3 is an ortholog of members of the human ATPase H+/K+ transporting family including ATP12A and ATP1 (ATPase Na+/K+ transporting subunits) family including ATP1A1; RNA sequencing and microarray studies indicate that catp-3 is affected by Ethanol, Nitric Oxide, 1-methylnicotinamide, Mercuric Chloride, Rotenone, Sodium arsenite, D-glucose, Levamisole, Resveratrol, Deoxyglucose, Chlorpyrifos, Diazinon, Quercetin, Humic substances, R24, Dafa#1, adsorbable organic bromine compounds, and Sirolimus; tiling array, RNA sequencing, and microarray studies indicate that catp-3 is enriched in the hypodermis and hermaphrodite-specific tissues.
sqrd-1 is an ortholog of human SQRDL (sulfide quinone reductase-like (yeast)) and RP11-96O20.4; sqrd-1 is predicted to have oxidoreductase activity, based on protein domain information.

prdx-2 encodes one of two C. elegans typical 2-Cys peroxiredoxins, peroxidase enzymes that reduce hydrogen peroxide and contribute to the oxidative-stress response of multicellular organisms; loss of  prdx-2 activity results in increased sensitivity to sublethal doses of hydrogen peroxide and increased resistance to heavy metals,  likely via increased expression of Phase II detoxification enzymes  such as GCS-1 in a SKN-1-independent manner; in addition, loss of prdx-2 results in decreased longevity and conditions that elevate  levels of hyperoxidized PRDX-2 result in increased thermotolerance; PRDX-2 is expressed from early embryogenesis through postembryonic development, where it is detected in the intestine, gonad, and neurons; PRDX-2 appears to be a cytoplasmic protein, excluded from the nucleus; intestinal expression of PRDX-2 is necessary and sufficient for survival in the presence of hydrogen peroxide, but cannot rescue the heavy-metal resistance and longevity phenotypes of prdx-2 mutants.

fce-2 encodes an ortholog of 'farnesylated-proteins converting enzyme 2' (FACE-2), and thus probably enables post-translational processing of proteins (such as LET-60/RAS) carrying a C-terminal CaaX motif; FCE-2 protein probably accounts for the tosylphenylalanylchloromethane-sensitive, EDTA-insensitive component of CaaX-proteolytic activity in membrane extracts from C. elegans; FCE-2 can cleave a farnesylated peptide in vitro; Rce1p, the S. cerevisiae homolog of FCE-2, is directly involved in the C-terminal processing of farnesylated a-factor mating pheromone, and transgenic fce-2 rescues the mating defect of mutant yeast lacking both the Ste24p and the Rce1p CaaX-proteases.
fmo-5 encodes a flavin-containing monoxygenase homologous to human FMO1, FMO2, and FMO3 (OMIM:602079, mutated in trimethylaminuria).
K09H11.7 is an ortholog of human PDXP (pyridoxal phosphatase) and PGP (phosphoglycolate phosphatase); K09H11.7 is predicted to have phosphatase activity, based on protein domain information.
